rComments: hotttie!  Loved his documentary course. Laid back & open minded.
Insightful and interesting.  The lectures sometimes seemed to drag on but for the most part it was engaging.

This was a survey course, which was reflected in the very vague lectures which were difficult to distill any notes from. However, the essay assignment was clear and the tests were manageable. He is very fond of the phrase "the notion of". :)
Great prof! Very helpful and quite enthusiastic about lecture material. THis is the first time I had him, but he is great and I will def. take any of his courses again. An asset to UTSC.

MacRae is a really great prof and a super guy. Not only is he extremely approachable and friendly, but he is very knowledgeable and conducts interesting lectures. I've really enjoyed taking this class with him.
